Great sweets / baked goods.

The drip coffee is very acidic. Do not buy. Coffee in general is overpriced.

If we come again I'll try a latte But if these prices wow....

This was my first time here. They open at 6.30am and when I come back I will be getting there as close to that time as possible. Their amazing baked goods rotate so if you want something specific you best get there when they open. I got there around 8.30 and the place was mostly full inside of patrons enjoying their goodies and a line. It took about 20plus minutes, but it was worth the wait! We had their signature sourdough bread, a raised donut(AMAZING), a pumpkin mocha cream cheese muffin(to die for!!), a chocolate chip cookie(good), a savory cruffin(O.M.Goodness, so yummy), and a couple flavored lattes(very, very good). This place is absolutely worth getting up early for and the 25 min drive, hands down!!

Good bakery overall. Sucks that you come here in the middle of the day and they run out of breads. Makes me want skip this place and just go to copain even tho its futher.

I love the bakery and the food. Everything is amazing and tastes good. Just one thing. I wish they had focaccia bread and sourdough bread hourly. There are days I come in and they don’t have any bread options and say it’ll be ready at around 11pm, or some days I’ll come in and they will be sold out sooooo early which then I am never able to get bread at this bakery. It’s very frustrating when you drive out to the bakery and they don’t have what they say they are supposed to have.

Delicious local coffee spot, the cortado was about average however the pastries are a must try. It was fresh light and flavorful. The only thing I wish they would do is label the pastries so we wouldn’t have to ask what it is. Overall, I would try them again.

reviews_data.review_text: The absolute BEST!

I love all the treats at Virtuoso! I live out of state and do not have a bakery to this excellent standard at home. The bakery uses quality ingredients and puts a lot of love in their products.  My sister Carrie introduced me to this extraordinary bakery.  I have enjoyed all of the pastries,  pies, breads, but my favorite is the oatmeal raisin cookie. My daughter loves the bagel bombs and requests them when we visit.  Thank you for your kindness and your goodies have become a tradition at our family gatherings.
Great little gem! Awesome Sourdough and pastries. Always lovely service

If they have a topped focaccia, get it. You won’t be disappointed. Honestly, you won’t be disappointed with anything they have. Coffee cakes. Cheese danishes. Pretzel croissants. Chocolate almond croissants. Even a simple brioche donut. It’s all fantastic and made with excellence. Don’t get me started on their coffee. It’s divine. And all the syrups are made from scratch. I’m spoiled to their vanilla. And if you come regularly, they will learn your name and preferences. Fabulous experience all around!

Fresh bread and baked treats, great coffee! Small but super cozy inside. Perfect place to grab a cup of coffee with a friend. The only downside - this place is too far away from me to walk there every day!

Wow this place is just incredible. Every time
I pass it I need to convince myself not to go in. My twins LOVEEE the pastries and I’m a happy mama guilt free because of the great ingredients. This is a go to place whenever we have visitors out of town. Yes it’s on the more expensive side but time is money and have you ever made anything sourdough…if not then you can’t complain. We easily spend $$$ on who knows what without an extra thought about it, and then expect a bakery to be cheap.

Very happy to have this little gem in our little town. Thank you for your hard work
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for this ❤️❤️❤️

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent sourdough bread. Can't wait to good back and try some more items. The service was fast and friendly. The atmosphere was inviting and relaxing. I highly recommend!

I was almost offended when I bought two almond croissants, and two danish for $36 until I felt how heavy the box was and then proceeded to absolutely devour one the croissants as soon as I got home. It was so good omg, definitely felt like I had eaten a whole breakfast meal with my coffee. The shop is a little tucked away from the main Waxhaw "strip" underneath this large tree and I wouldn't have known it was there until I browsed our area in Google maps and I'm glad I did.  They sell out of bread later in the afternoon so it's best you go in the morning but be aware there may be a line during the weekend. One of the better food offerings in Waxhaw and the employees are always pleasant unlike the pizza place next door.  I'd definitely recommend them!

reviews_data.review_text: I travel quite a bit for work and try to always find a local bakery to quiet down my growling stomach. This has, hands down,  been one of the best places I've been to. The hype is real. The staff was so lovely and the pateries were divine. I just devoured the pumpkin cruffin. It was like fall and a hug all wrapped up in a pretty teal box. I'm excited to keep trying my box of treats as the days go on. This will be a must stop for me whenever I am nearby.

Not only are the baked goods delicious, but the staff here is really lovely. I used to take my special needs little brother here. He loved it and the workers always took time to be really sweet to him. They heard that he passed away and the next time I dropped by the bakery they sent me home with a TON of baked goods to share with my family. It was unbelievably kind and we were very touched. Definitely worth trying their food and supporting these wonderful people.

This place is a gem! It’s one place I always bring guests from out of town and they’re always clamoring to come back. In fact, one friend brought several loaves of stuffed sourdough and focaccia on her flight back to Naples, FL so she could share with her family! I come here regularly and could eat here daily if it weren’t dangerous for my pocketbook and my wasteline.

I recently had a little hiccup with an order of bread (so rare) and msg’d them, and they immediately rectified the situation. Then the sweet staff went above and beyond and insisted I have a cookie on the house as well. Totally unnecessary but their chocolate chunk cookies are divine sooo I couldn’t turn down the kindness. This is one of my favorite places to eat in the area and the best bakery hands down. I hope they never leave!

I’ve been here when people from Europe said the quality was as good as anything there! They have totally ruined me for other baked goods…not even tempted elsewhere. This little gem of a bakery is amazing! Pastries and breads change daily and they certainly have something for everyone.  We happen to LOVE the flat Stanley’s, bread pudding, cookies and coffee - but there’s so many more delicious treats.

Everything is fresh, fresh, FRESH!!! Highly recommend!!

Everything here was stunning from the breads to the pastries and the staff were so welcoming. My friend and I stopped in here yesterday specifically for fig danishes since figs are in season but ended up trying a couple of other baked goods as well. The bakery is located in the cutest little town and it looks like a house that was converted into a bakery. The location, design, and seating inside really tied together that homey feeling.

There was a line when we arrived but they kept it moving pretty quick. One thing that's for sure is this bakery has a strong backbone from the local and surrounding communities. We were here from around 8am to 12pm on a Saturday hanging out and eating pastries, and there was a consistent flow of customers which we loved to see. After trying everything though, we can now see why!

We ordered a croissant, fig danish, pan au chocolat, and a cheddar biscuit. The fig danish had to have been our favorite by far. The cream cheese filling was so addicting and the crumble on top added the perfect texture component. However, the croissant almost beat out the fig danish. The top was flakey with a soft buttery inside and the bottom had a nice crunchy base. Similar to the croissant, the pan au chocolat had a soft buttery interior. It also had the ultimate crunch on top, and I loved the dark rich chocolate they used on the inside. Finally, we have the cheddar biscuit. I don't eat biscuits often so not sure what to base this off but it was still pretty good for what it was and my friend said she loved it.

Virtuoso Breadworks is truly an amazing bakery and if someone asks where to go for baked goods in the area, I'm going to send them here first! We will definitely be back in the future to try their focaccia and other seasonal pastries. I also have to give them bonus points for having a wheelchair/handicap accessible walkway into the bakery. As someone who is on crutches at the moment, this is super convenient and makes life a lot easier!

Complete and utter disappointment. Heard such hype about this place so drove 45 minutes to check it out and I wish I had just gone to 7/11 instead. Nothing spectacular about the food all. Then to make matters worse, we arrived at 11am and they didn't have any cinnamon rolls, cheese Danish, raisin bread and a few other items. I understand demand but the dang place still had over 6hrs left of operating time and they weren't even going to make any more. Wish I could get back the time and energy I wasted driving there and waiting in line.

I am a world traveler, and foodie. I have eaten some pretty amazing things from some pretty incredible chefs, but the two chef/owners here definitely score on the top of my list. The creations that their team comes up with are so innovative and creative. I have never found a pastry or bread that I didn’t salivate over from here. The name Virtuoso is definitely apropos for this place. They aren’t just experts in their food, they are experts in our community and the hospitality that they provide. Virtuoso is a place where if you walk in often enough, they will greet you by name and know what you’re drinking. It’s a place you can meet a client for coffee or a friend for a pick me up snack. Moms gather here with their toddlers and enjoy a mom’s morning out. On Saturday’s the line is wrapped around the building because it’s that good and worth the wait. It’s a place that looks out for our community and that our community looks out for in return.
My highest recommendation for Ben, Lauren, their entire team and every creation they put out there.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is the absolute best!  From the bread, to the coffee, to the goodies, it cannot be topped.  The staff is always so friendly and helpful, too.
Excellent baked goods. I have never been disappointed by anything I’ve tried.
The absolute best bread in NC, hands down. Virtuoso is so good that its location was a considerable factor in choosing Waxhaw as our home.
Went here twice in one week! Everything we got was absolutely delicious. Highly recommend!
Loved everything I've tried here. Friendly folks behind the counter also.
Everything is delicious... especially the cinnamon rolls, raisin bread, cruffins, bagel bombs, cream cheese danishes, lattes, americanos...you get the idea.
Almond croissants were  delicious!!!
Cute little place with so many options.  Everything we ordered was yum. I specifically loved the almond croissant. I highly recommend this place.

Just wow.  I'm from out of town and I come to this bakery every year when I visit my father. Amazing croissants and coffee!! Their savory bread loafs are to die for!!! My taste buds miss them already.
absolutely fantastic fig danish
Fabulous stuff, but get there early otherwise slim Pickens

Great local bakery. You need to get there early on Saturdays because everyone knows how amazing this place is, and things WILL sell out. That said, there’s no bad choice to be made here. The cookies, croissants, stuffed pretzels and seasonal Danish pastries are all delish, but the cardamom bun is my favorite. The people that work there are genuinely nice folks.
If you don't get their sourdough, you're out of your mind! I also really enjoyed their cold brew. And the staff was so friendly. What a gem!!
Just the best, all around. It's an absolute privilege to have this bakery so close. We love the food and the people of Virtuoso!

So good! Better than good! Last week was the first time and now I'm going every week.

I love everything about this place!

The chai tea is a must, and the savory croissants never disappoint. And  BONUS- the service is as good as the food. Absolutely the best downtown Waxhaw has to offer!
Amazing place!!!! Love it!!!! Kind staff and OUT OF THIS WORLD FOOD!!!!
One of my favorite places on the planet!!!
A great little gem. Fresh baked breads and simple coffee orders. Low key and refreshing.

Incredible coffee shop / bakery in Waxhaw. The team was such a joy to be around, and really made a home-like atmosphere. Great coffee with a wide range of options, and their baked goods are to die for.

I hope they keep on with with what they're doing and get much more business!!

Very tasty fresh baked goods and coffees.
Quaint little locality well worth the visit!!
This is the most amazing place.  The pastries are so good!!!  I would highly recommend this place!!!

This place has absolutely ruined any other bread I’ve ever gotten. They have both classic products, as well as creative ideas that are incomparable to anything else in the area, not to mention the wonderful customer service that that makes you feel at home, regardless if it’s your first visit or thousandth.
Very good cinnamin, cinoman, cinnomen,... Breakfast swirls.
Nice to have a place so close to home where we can get fresh baked breads, danishes, bagel bombs, and a variety of treats

My husband and I went to Virtuoso’s for the first time today and it was amazing! We got the coffee cake, cardamon bun, and cinnamon bun! Everything was so delicious and the staff at the counter were extremely nice and helpful! Highly recommend!
Fantastic baked goods and coffee!
Always great!

People are friendly, talkative, quick and helpful.  Items all look fantastic.  Chocolate Croissant is so buttery and flaky and delicious could use a little more chocolate but with the cinnamon roll latte, the chocolate notes from the latte covered and blended any missing elsewhere.  Latte was perfect and couldnt have been better.  Would recommend here anytime. Fruit tart is for a friend if it makes it there.  Levels fantastically better then anywhere else including a starbucks addiction.

I have had some of the best eating experiences here in my life. The linzer cookies are my absolute favorite. But holy cannolli you need to eat the focaccia bread!! It. Is. Life. Changing. (I am normally gluten free but I make exceptions for Virtuoso😂). Also a big fan of their flat whites and lattes.
Basically if you are in the area you need to swing by!
Great Latte and amazing baked breads!
Delicious, quick. Laid back
Delicious!
Great service, everything we had was delicious. 👍🏾

I went there with my family yesterday afternoon for the first time after my wife share great things about it. It was around 4 pm and the business hours are until 5:30 pm.
The door was open and as we came in the person attending was not friendly saying that they were sold out and we forgot to lock the door,  without any kindness.
We ordered some drinks but the person was in a hurry to close the place 1:30h before the closing time and invited us to leave as soon as the beverages were ready (my son was just playing Pacman but she was pretty bold asking us to leave). It was a very unpleasant experience.

Drove for about 40 min to this place to try the pastries and it did not disappoint. Got bagel bomb, tomato feta cheese danish, cranberry cheese danish, cardamom bun, butter croissant and chocolate croissant. Their flavors are good, savory pastries are well seasoned and sweet ones were well balanced, loved the fact that the sweet ones are not extremely sweet. Croissants were really flaky with several layers, the butter flavor was good, they are now in my top places for croissants in NC.
I only wished they were closer to Charlotte area.
Delicious - be sure to follow their social media to know what fresh yummy things are available that day. Great small town feel that will put a smile on your face.
How can I love this place more??  Delicious pastries and breads have me trying to budget so I don’t spend my entire paycheck here!
Delicious bread! 😋
Not even kidding…the VERY best pastries I have ever had anywhere. 😍😍😍

Ok, the pastries are good. But if your service doesn't match, that is a bummer for the business. I was visiting with family and stocked up... we paid $60 for our pastries and left $5 in tip (no one had to make a drink ... just bag up the pastries). Then as we were leaving, my sister asked for a cup of water. She was asked for 25 cents for the cup. I was shocked. 25 cents is no big deal obviously, but when you have a customer making a huge order, tipping well and don't just offer the cup of water with a smile, that's an issue. Next time, no tip and I'll consider going else where. I hope this comment will be taken in a constructive way. To be fair, the pastries were delicious.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Sharon, I do sincerely apologize for this experience this isn't what myself or Ben would have done.   We will relay this to the team to ensure this doesn't  happen again. Thank you for bringing this to our attention as this does not reflect the standards of service we wish to uphold for Virtuoso Breadworks

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious fresh baked goodies with friendly staff. Definitely recommend!
Amazing place. Best bakery and delicious coffee. They make syrups in house. Freshest ingredients. We love this place!
Bagel bomb was the best today, so fresh.  Cute little Cafe environment and very friendly staff!
Incredible cheese stuffed pretzels! Best pretzel I’ve ever had.
Best little bakery in the area. Very busy Saturday  mornings.
Excellent place. They offered free muffins when we were there. The muffins were not the prettiest but tasted amazing. The banana bread we purchased was also amazing.
Fresh, great tasting pastries and well made drinks in a cute setting. Run, don’t walk!
Amazing neighborhood treasure... delicious different choices every day... consistently good with new surprises all the time
The filled Donuts are amazing as well the croissants...I loved it and so did the kids
Love this place. Super happy great service ❤️
This place is wonderful!! You will wait in line, but it is so worth it!!! Get a Cruffin and stuffed pretzel. I had a cold brew with Mexican chocolate  - fantastically perfect!!

Such a cute little bakery, the ambience is so Waxhaw. I got the bagel bomb with a cream cheese surprise and it was so tasty. It was obviously made fresh.

There's indoor and outdoor seating. There's mobility access to the bakery (ramp)
By far in a way this is the best bakery in town. It even tops most of the bakeries in Charlotte. You just have to get there early because the good stuff goes quick!
Wow! Wow! 1st time here. Super friendly staff.  The baked goods were phenomenal!  Can't wait to try the bread
This place is amazing! Staff is very friendly and helpful. Everything I have tried has been fresh and delicious.
Best coffe best everything
Woah this spot is filled with THe best selection of baked goods in the entire region! Even better they serve local coffee and have the best and most helpful staff!  Must visit!
1st visit.  The glazed donut lemon flavor of the day was fluffy and delicious

I drive out here from Ballantyne (which takes me 20 minutes one way) once a week to get their amazing sour dough bread and other baked goods. Today I stopped by and got their white chocolate matcha donut. OMG! Best donut I tried! I'm hooked for life.
Cute place with great service and even more amazing baked goods. Highly recommend.
A great place for coffee, snacks, and bread. I loved the soft pretzel with pepper jack cheese!
As good it gets. We've lived in and traveled throughout Europe and this bakery I'd put up against anything I've ever had and confidently bet on. We're lucky to have them local.

Amazing!! Every time we come here the pastries are exceptional. We love everything we’ve ever tried. Breads, etc. The croissants are swoon worthy. Definitely the best we’ve had outside of Paris. There isn’t another bakery anywhere around like this. We love the owners and their story. We love the little quirky house. It’s a gem.

Run, don't walk(!) to get some of the best pastries and bread I've had in the last few years -- and they make a mean dirty chai & vanilla latte. Worth waking up early on a Saturday to get a cruffin or kouign amman or whatever bite of joy is in the case. Virtuoso is a gem in the crown jewels of Waxhaw!
Yummy!  That is all!
Pastries are delicious and the service is always great! This is a gem of a bakery!

I love this place for so many reasons. The staff is so fun, the menu is always creative and you can taste the love that’s poured into each item. The coffee is fantastic and the dining area is clean, comfortable and well designed. Hands down the best bakery in town.
Amazing experience from start to finish! You can’t go wrong with anything they make!
Everything baked with love and the staff is incredible. I haven’t had anything that wasn’t superb. We are so lucky to have this fantastic bakery in our community!
Absolutely delicious sourdough. The cruffins are to die for! Can’t wait to try those bagel bombs that everyone is raving about!
I’m a weekly customer! Service and baked goods are 10/10. You can’t find better anywhere else!

Stopped in for the first time today, got a loaf of sourdough bread and a few of the pretzels. The smell of it all in my car drove me to eat one pretzel on the way home. Tried the sourdough, which tastes AMAZING! True sourdough like you would find in San Francisco used as a classic chowder bread bowl! Definitely will be back again to try more things soon!
Love it the staff there is so friendly and the pastas there are great
Best cheese danish I’ve ever had !!! Can’t wait to go back and try their other options.
A great addition to Waxhaw. Solid coffee options and a wonderful select of bread in a quaint, comfortable setting. The staff is very friendly as well.
Best place ever. However they describe the taste is exactly what to expect.  Staff is friendly.

Such a treasure! We are so lucky having this shop here in Waxhaw. We made outstanding French toast this morning, maybe the best we've ever had.

Strongly recommended!
Freaking great baked goods!!!!!
Everything looked gorgeous, I am new to the area and was told to visit, so glad I did, everything looked delicious. The sour dough is fantastic.

The best bread (especially the sourdough) we have ever had. Everything in this little gem in Waxhaw is delicious. The strawberry danish, bagel bombs are out of this world. We had them bake an apple pie for Christmas and it was fantastic. Amazing bakers and wonderful customer service.
Their baked goodies are delicious!!! Go as early as possible to get the best selection. You won't be disappointed.
Traveled from kannapolis to get some baked goods and totally worth it!!
Delicious pastries, bread and coffee with friendly staff. Loved this local little gem!
My favorite bakery in the Charlotte area

I get chills when I go here, because places like this are so necessary for the future. Over the years businesses have traded quality for quantity in the pursuit of making more profit.

The quality of food when it is mass produced is just inferior, and people don't even truly know what "good" food made with wholesome ingredients tastes like anymore.

Virtuoso Breadworks embodies quality food. You can taste the purity of the ingredients and the passion put into the process of creating each item. Bravo!

Thank you so much for being in business!
Best bakery in town! Always fresh, delicious and friendly!
By far the best bakery in the Charlotte region. The muffins are insane and they always experiment with new items all the time.  We're so happy we've found this hidden jem.

Oh wow!  Virtuoso is ALWAYS 5 stars for our family, but that's only because we can't rate them at 6... or 10!  10! would be appropriate.

We have NEVER enjoyed such wonderful baked goods!  We ordered several items to complement our Thanksgiving dinner, but I'm reporting today on the pecan 🥧!  Oh my!!! 😋👍

✅ I could spend all day telling you how AMAZING & DELICIOUS the food is here!🥮🍪🥧🍮 I didn’t take any photos of the treats because I eat them before I leave the parking lot, and I’m not kidding Haha. 👌 So many different kinds that are fresh daily and they change often enough so you can always try something new! Don’t hesitate to go, seriously ✅

This place is so delicious. I have never seen so many layers in a croissant. My favorite is the almond, but honestly everything is amazing. The staff are friendly , helpful and energetic. I find this super awesome since they go to work so early every morning. One of my favorite businesses in our little town.
Must try everything! If you live in Charlotte it is definitely worth the drive. Eat there, bring home, repeat!
We love everything we have tried here and we have tried a lot of things. Some of my favorites are their focaccia breads, bagel bombs, chocolate croissants and the danishes.
Very very good!❤ Love that the coffee flavors are all house made!
I love this place! Everything is so delicious and the staff is just the best!
Virtuoso makes the best chocolate dairy-free cookies you'll ever have. And Amelya is the bomb. Love this place!
Staff has always been friendly and food has been excellent!  You will not be disappointed!

You could not ask for a better or more friendly staff, several choices the day we went. Everything we got was amazing. You can tell this is not some mass produced product. This is top quality with that wonderful homemade right out of the oven flavor. Do yourself a favor and stop by soon, you will understand why they have the following they do!
The perfect place for an amazing pastry and coffee.  Plus great outdoor seating with some play areas to entertain the kids.
Amazing little bakery, if you're within 100 miles this should be on your itinerary!

The freaking cutest. I love this place. Just one smell and you want one of everything. Love that the bakery rotates and makes something new each day. I could rave about this bakery all day long but I’m too busy eating their treats right now.
Best. Cinnamon. Rolls. Ever. Everything else is great too, but the cinnamon rolls are literally the best I’ve ever had.
Amazing pastries!

This bakery is absolutely outrageous. I can't even put into words how incredible these pastries/bread are. They are always changing the menu which means I always have a new favorite. Staff is friendly and fun and I highly recommend paying this place a visit! 🤤

This place will blow your mind. It's literally one of a kind and I'm not joking when I say that I've never had baked goods this delicious. Couldn't recommend any higher, you've gotta try it for yourself.
Awesome staff!!!

Absolutely amazing local bakery with different features everyday! The stuffed English muffin is by far a family favorite! Recently had a pineapple peach danish and it was absolutely AMAZING. Staff is always kind and pleasant. Espresso drink needs a little help though.
Highly recommend! We had a couple pastries and coffee. They were all great but any that include their croissant dough is top of the list! Layers on layers on layers. Will definitely go back.
Amazing food!  The sausage wrapped in English muffin is wonderful!  Stop in, you won't regret it!
Best caramel latte Ive had that wasn't in my own coffee shop! The bread and pastries are fabulous. I had a bacon cheddar brioche, a croissant and a loaf of sourdough and each was excellent!
Go here if you want excellent banana bread, fabulous chocolate brownies, and refreshingly delicious iced chai tea and iced coffee!! A gem in Waxhaw! A new favorite for us, and great service!
They have some delicious pastries. Just wish things moved a little quicker inside. We went on a Saturday and there was a line. Overall, great sweets and coffee though.
You walk in and the smell of this place is HEAVENLY!! Customer service was amazing, coffee delicious and pastries  are scrumptious!!
You want to buy the best bread and pastries come here
Very busy always. Pastries are delicious.
This place.... is perfect. Just perfect.

Top quality bakery all round. Their selection is amazing and it’s served with a huge smile from everyone there. Jennie was awesome and took customer service to another level. Super Impressed and Highly recommend this place to anyone!!
Love everything they make. The sourdough is awesome. Picked up an order of hot cross buns today and they are the best! Totally exceeded my expectations.
Great coffee and pastries! The staff was super great and understanding when I mentioned my peanut allergy. I also really appreciate the milk alternatives available too!
AMAZING coffee and pastries!!!
Pastries are amazing but coffee was really nasty, they add plain whole milk . Paying $6 for a small cup of coffee for  a low quality ingredients is a reap off .
Waxhaw is so lucky to have this gem. Well worth the visit...just for the viennoissrie alone - hand laminated (not machine rolled.)
Love the place, very kind people and service
Great place. Staff extremely friendly and helpful. Great sourdough bread. The rye bread was excellent. The pastries were delicious.

We grab breakfast from the bakery every Saturday morning and sometimes during the week! I also will get a bunch of different things for team meetings for my law firm. The bagel bombs, stuffed English muffins, crescent cups, and danishes are our favorite!!! Absolutely never disappointed!
Delightful staff and delicious breads, croissants, treats, coffee and teas!

It is hard to leave this wonderful bakery without a bag full of goodies. The sourdough breads are perfect for sandwiches and morning toast with jelly. My kids are very picky but love the bagel bombs and croissants.  For those with a sweet tooth, you have to try it the twice baked croissants and brown sugar cookies.  I could go on and on but you really need to stop by and try something. I promise you won’t be disappointed.
Always warm and kind and great bread/ pasteries/ goodies and coffee.

I just got home from the most amazing bakery! Virtuoso breadworks, you absolutely captured my full attention. We got a jalapeño bagel bomb to which my husband said was one of the best things he’s ever eaten (mind you it was still warm and melty when we got home). We also got regular and apple cinnamon rolls, an almond croissant, Irish cheddar sourdough loaf and coffee. Every single last crumb was delicious. And the coffee too, probably the best latte I’ve ever had. So smooth. I myself am also a baker and am ALWAYS disappointed when I get bread and pastries outside of my own kitchen because I never feel like they are as good as my own. Today was different. VIRTUOSO you will now forever be in my weekly lineup. We probably will have to get one of everything until we try it all. My husband seriously wants to go back and get every jalapeño bomb in the case. And if what I said wasn’t enough already, the staff was so absolutely friendly and you could tell instantly that they have a LOVE for their craft. Please stop at all costs and support this amazing business. We’ll probably be back this afternoon.

Stopped in today after hearing my co-worker rave about this place. Certainly worth the drive from Fort Mill! Gorgeous loaves of sourdough bread and tasty pastries. The raspberry cruffin was divine! The staff are just as sweet as their creations. Will be visiting again very soon!
Love the Lemon thumbprints

After hearing lots of great things about this place, we decided to check it out. It's a bit of a drive for us, so we planned a hike in the area too.

Covid-19: I was actually not very comfortable here. We waited in line for probably 20-25 minutes in a very small, and pretty crowded converted house. The worst part was that they have couches for people to eat at right next to where you have to wait in line. While we were there, two people were just sitting on them talking, not wearing masks (they had clearly finished eating a while ago). Given the small area and that there's no way to get takeout quickly, it would be safer if they didn't have people eating inside right now.

Once we got to the front of the line, the staff was very friendly and described everything they had. We ended up getting a sourdough english muffin that was stuffed with sausage, bread pudding, and a dulce de leche cruffin.

The english muffin sandwich thing was delicious. It wasn't served warm, but we still loved it cold. I might take it home and warm it up next time. The bread pudding was pretty good too.

The cruffin was not good. It was very dry and didn't have a lot of dulce de leche.

I'd love to come back and try some more of their savory items because I think that's where they really shine.

I'm not rateing this place on the food I'm rateting this place on the times that it's open and closed worse then bankers hours cannot believe on a Sunday morning closed never heard of a bakery being closed on a Sunday morning
reviews_data.owner_answer: We have 3 children at home and believe in making time for family. All of our products are handmade, in house and we are old school. If we were open on Sunday, we would never have a day off. I'm sorry that you feel the need to rate is based on when we are open and not on the quality of our products. We would be more than happy to suggest some of our items and give reheat instructions so you can enjoy our products on a Sunday. Also, there aren't any banks around here open on a Sunday, so 7-530 5 days a week seems pretty reasonable for a small family owned and operated business.

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious treats. Unique coffee and tea selection

So many delicious choices. Hard to just get one thing! Today's picks: English muffins, raspberry cheese Danish, butter croissant, chocolate croissant, savory stuffed croissant. Can't wait to get them in my belly 😊
Great coffee. Great cinnamon raisin bread. Julia was wonderful.

We must have come when they were having an off day. There was only one other patron in the store and the staff took a while to acknowledge that we were there.  However, once we were acknowledged the lady was extremely friendly. The selections were very limited by 2pm on a Tuesday.  We didn’t buy any bread products due to limited selection so we bought drinks. The drinks were small, overpriced and tasted watered down (lacked flavor). Overall for the price I would not go back.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the feedback. There are days we unexpectedly sell out of many things very early. Our apologies that there wasn't a better selection available! We recently installed a brand new espresso machine and are working on our training program and drink menu to ensure this doesn't happen again.

reviews_data.review_text: A co-worker just brought us some cookies as a Christmas gift and o-m-g!! They are SO delicious! Way to go. Highly recommend!

Great food/coffee,  friendly staff - recommend avoiding if busy during the pandemic, as there is basically no way to effectively distance inside. I stop by, and if busy, I just leave and come back another time.
Great pastries!

Love this little gem! Everyone in there is so friendly and so caring. Love that they actually take the time to ask you how your day/week is going (even when they are busy and don’t rush you out). The BEST pastries and breads ever and best chai lattes.

The ladies here were extremely inviting, the coffee was great, and there so many options for pastries and sweets. I will definitely be making this a frequently visited local business. The smells alone make a stop worth while!
The staff is wonderful. Will gladly drive all the way to Waxhaw for this place.
Best pastries in Union County
Most bakeries produce good cookies because most cookies are good. Their cookies are, “out of this world  fabulous! Try them all!
Excellent Staff, excellent food!!
Nice to have an amazing place in my awesome hometown of Waxhaw!  Their chocolate croissants are huge and delicious!

My favorite bakery in waxhaw! My intention is to go in for one pastry and I always I end up leaving with a whole box because everything always looks so good. And it always tastes so good. The best quality & best ingredients make this bakery a star!!
I had the everything bagel bomb, it might be the most amazing bagel I've ever had. The staff is super nice and helpful. My daughter has a nut allergy and they were able to accommodate her needs

Holy Smokes!!! This is the real deal. I live in Charlotte and make it a point to drive out and devour these delightful, delicious, fresh gifts from the bakery gods. Seriously though, the owners are humble, honest and talented as they come. Their love is poured into each croissant, cruffin and sourdough loaf. Don't get me started on the Stuffed English Muffins and the Bagel Bombs!!! Virtuoso gives 2020 hope to the community that we all need to treat ourselves.

Stopped by for coffee and a sweet treat. Had a cheese struesel croissant, took home a loaf of cinnamon raisin bread as well. The croissant was  melt in my mouth, delicious! The raisin bread was light, fluffy, with a nice crust. Compliments to the Baker. The employees were friendly and helpful. They took time to tell me about each of the bakery items. I will return!

reviews_data.review_text: The absolute BEST!

I love all the treats at Virtuoso! I live out of state and do not have a bakery to this excellent standard at home. The bakery uses quality ingredients and puts a lot of love in their products.  My sister Carrie introduced me to this extraordinary bakery.  I have enjoyed all of the pastries,  pies, breads, but my favorite is the oatmeal raisin cookie. My daughter loves the bagel bombs and requests them when we visit.  Thank you for your kindness and your goodies have become a tradition at our family gatherings.
Great little gem! Awesome Sourdough and pastries. Always lovely service

My friend and I stopped in here yesterday specifically for fig danishes since figs are in season but ended up trying a couple of other baked goods as well. There was a line when we arrived but they kept it moving pretty quick. One thing that's for sure is this bakery has a strong backbone from the local and surrounding communities. We were here from around 8am to 12pm on a Saturday hanging out and eating pastries, and there was a consistent flow of customers which we loved to see. We ordered a croissant, fig danish, pan au chocolat, and a cheddar biscuit. The fig danish had to have been our favorite by far. The cream cheese filling was so addicting and the crumble on top added the perfect texture component. However, the croissant almost beat out the fig danish. The top was flakey with a soft buttery inside and the bottom had a nice crunchy base. Similar to the croissant, the pan au chocolat had a soft buttery interior. It also had the ultimate crunch on top, and I loved the dark rich chocolate they used on the inside. Finally, we have the cheddar biscuit. I don't eat biscuits often so not sure what to base this off but it was still pretty good for what it was and my friend said she loved it.

I hope they keep on with with what they're doing and get much more business!!

Very tasty fresh baked goods and coffees.
Quaint little locality well worth the visit!!
This is the most amazing place.  The pastries are so good!!!  I would highly recommend this place!!!

This place has absolutely ruined any other bread I’ve ever gotten. They have both classic products, as well as creative ideas that are incomparable to anything else in the area, not to mention the wonderful customer service that that makes you feel at home, regardless if it’s your first visit or thousandth.
Very good cinnamin, cinoman, cinnomen,... Breakfast swirls.
Nice to have a place so close to home where we can get fresh baked breads, danishes, bagel bombs, and a variety of treats

My husband and I went to Virtuoso’s for the first time today and it was amazing! We got the coffee cake, cardamon bun, and cinnamon bun! Everything was so delicious and the staff at the counter were extremely nice and helpful! Highly recommend!
Fantastic baked goods and coffee!
Always great!

People are friendly, talkative, quick and helpful.  Items all look fantastic.  Chocolate Croissant is so buttery and flaky and delicious could use a little more chocolate but with the cinnamon roll latte, the chocolate notes from the latte covered and blended any missing elsewhere.  Latte was perfect and couldnt have been better.  Would recommend here anytime. Fruit tart is for a friend if it makes it there.  Levels fantastically better then anywhere else including a starbucks addiction.

I have had some of the best eating experiences here in my life. The linzer cookies are my absolute favorite. But holy cannolli you need to eat the focaccia bread!! It. Is. Life. Changing. (I am normally gluten free but I make exceptions for Virtuoso😂). Also a big fan of their flat whites and lattes.
Basically if you are in the area you need to swing by!
Great Latte and amazing baked breads!
Delicious, quick. Laid back
Delicious!
Great service, everything we had was delicious. 👍🏾

I went there with my family yesterday afternoon for the first time after my wife share great things about it. It was around 4 pm and the business hours are until 5:30 pm.
The door was open and as we came in the person attending was not friendly saying that they were sold out and we forgot to lock the door,  without any kindness.
We ordered some drinks but the person was in a hurry to close the place 1:30h before the closing time and invited us to leave as soon as the beverages were ready (my son was just playing Pacman but she was pretty bold asking us to leave). It was a very unpleasant experience.

Drove for about 40 min to this place to try the pastries and it did not disappoint. Got bagel bomb, tomato feta cheese danish, cranberry cheese danish, cardamom bun, butter croissant and chocolate croissant. Their flavors are good, savory pastries are well seasoned and sweet ones were well balanced, loved the fact that the sweet ones are not extremely sweet. Croissants were really flaky with several layers, the butter flavor was good, they are now in my top places for croissants in NC.
I only wished they were closer to Charlotte area.
Delicious - be sure to follow their social media to know what fresh yummy things are available that day. Great small town feel that will put a smile on your face.
How can I love this place more??  Delicious pastries and breads have me trying to budget so I don’t spend my entire paycheck here!
Delicious bread! 😋
Not even kidding…the VERY best pastries I have ever had anywhere. 😍😍😍

Ok, the pastries are good. But if your service doesn't match, that is a bummer for the business. I was visiting with family and stocked up... we paid $60 for our pastries and left $5 in tip (no one had to make a drink ... just bag up the pastries). Then as we were leaving, my sister asked for a cup of water. She was asked for 25 cents for the cup. I was shocked. 25 cents is no big deal obviously, but when you have a customer making a huge order, tipping well and don't just offer the cup of water with a smile, that's an issue. Next time, no tip and I'll consider going else where. I hope this comment will be taken in a constructive way. To be fair, the pastries were delicious.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Sharon, I do sincerely apologize for this experience this isn't what myself or Ben would have done.   We will relay this to the team to ensure this doesn't  happen again. Thank you for bringing this to our attention as this does not reflect the standards of service we wish to uphold for Virtuoso Breadworks

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious fresh baked goodies with friendly staff. Definitely recommend!
Amazing place. Best bakery and delicious coffee. They make syrups in house. Freshest ingredients. We love this place!
Bagel bomb was the best today, so fresh.  Cute little Cafe environment and very friendly staff!
Incredible cheese stuffed pretzels! Best pretzel I’ve ever had.
Best little bakery in the area. Very busy Saturday  mornings.
Excellent place. They offered free muffins when we were there. The muffins were not the prettiest but tasted amazing. The banana bread we purchased was also amazing.
Fresh, great tasting pastries and well made drinks in a cute setting. Run, don’t walk!
Amazing neighborhood treasure... delicious different choices every day... consistently good with new surprises all the time
The filled Donuts are amazing as well the croissants...I loved it and so did the kids
Love this place. Super happy great service ❤️
This place is wonderful!! You will wait in line, but it is so worth it!!! Get a Cruffin and stuffed pretzel. I had a cold brew with Mexican chocolate  - fantastically perfect!!

Such a cute little bakery, the ambience is so Waxhaw. I got the bagel bomb with a cream cheese surprise and it was so tasty. It was obviously made fresh.

There's indoor and outdoor seating. There's mobility access to the bakery (ramp)
By far in a way this is the best bakery in town. It even tops most of the bakeries in Charlotte. You just have to get there early because the good stuff goes quick!
Wow! Wow! 1st time here. Super friendly staff.  The baked goods were phenomenal!  Can't wait to try the bread
This place is amazing! Staff is very friendly and helpful. Everything I have tried has been fresh and delicious.
Best coffe best everything
Woah this spot is filled with THe best selection of baked goods in the entire region! Even better they serve local coffee and have the best and most helpful staff!  Must visit!
1st visit.  The glazed donut lemon flavor of the day was fluffy and delicious

I drive out here from Ballantyne (which takes me 20 minutes one way) once a week to get their amazing sour dough bread and other baked goods. Today I stopped by and got their white chocolate matcha donut. OMG! Best donut I tried! I'm hooked for life.
Cute place with great service and even more amazing baked goods. Highly recommend.
A great place for coffee, snacks, and bread. I loved the soft pretzel with pepper jack cheese!
As good it gets. We've lived in and traveled throughout Europe and this bakery I'd put up against anything I've ever had and confidently bet on. We're lucky to have them local.

Amazing!! Every time we come here the pastries are exceptional. We love everything we’ve ever tried. Breads, etc. The croissants are swoon worthy. Definitely the best we’ve had outside of Paris. There isn’t another bakery anywhere around like this. We love the owners and their story. We love the little quirky house. It’s a gem.

Run, don't walk(!) to get some of the best pastries and bread I've had in the last few years -- and they make a mean dirty chai & vanilla latte. Worth waking up early on a Saturday to get a cruffin or kouign amman or whatever bite of joy is in the case. Virtuoso is a gem in the crown jewels of Waxhaw!
Yummy!  That is all!
Pastries are delicious and the service is always great! This is a gem of a bakery!

I love this place for so many reasons. The staff is so fun, the menu is always creative and you can taste the love that’s poured into each item. The coffee is fantastic and the dining area is clean, comfortable and well designed. Hands down the best bakery in town.
Amazing experience from start to finish! You can’t go wrong with anything they make!
Everything baked with love and the staff is incredible. I haven’t had anything that wasn’t superb. We are so lucky to have this fantastic bakery in our community!
Absolutely delicious sourdough. The cruffins are to die for! Can’t wait to try those bagel bombs that everyone is raving about!
I’m a weekly customer! Service and baked goods are 10/10. You can’t find better anywhere else!

Stopped in for the first time today, got a loaf of sourdough bread and a few of the pretzels. The smell of it all in my car drove me to eat one pretzel on the way home. Tried the sourdough, which tastes AMAZING! True sourdough like you would find in San Francisco used as a classic chowder bread bowl! Definitely will be back again to try more things soon!
Love it the staff there is so friendly and the pastas there are great
Best cheese danish I’ve ever had !!! Can’t wait to go back and try their other options.
A great addition to Waxhaw. Solid coffee options and a wonderful select of bread in a quaint, comfortable setting. The staff is very friendly as well.
Best place ever. However they describe the taste is exactly what to expect.  Staff is friendly.

Such a treasure! We are so lucky having this shop here in Waxhaw. We made outstanding French toast this morning, maybe the best we've ever had.

Strongly recommended!
Freaking great baked goods!!!!!
Everything looked gorgeous, I am new to the area and was told to visit, so glad I did, everything looked delicious. The sour dough is fantastic.

The best bread (especially the sourdough) we have ever had. Everything in this little gem in Waxhaw is delicious. The strawberry danish, bagel bombs are out of this world. We had them bake an apple pie for Christmas and it was fantastic. Amazing bakers and wonderful customer service.
Their baked goodies are delicious!!! Go as early as possible to get the best selection. You won't be disappointed.
Traveled from kannapolis to get some baked goods and totally worth it!!
Delicious pastries, bread and coffee with friendly staff. Loved this local little gem!
My favorite bakery in the Charlotte area

I get chills when I go here, because places like this are so necessary for the future. Over the years businesses have traded quality for quantity in the pursuit of making more profit.

The quality of food when it is mass produced is just inferior, and people don't even truly know what "good" food made with wholesome ingredients tastes like anymore.

Virtuoso Breadworks embodies quality food. You can taste the purity of the ingredients and the passion put into the process of creating each item. Bravo!

Thank you so much for being in business!
Best bakery in town! Always fresh, delicious and friendly!
By far the best bakery in the Charlotte region. The muffins are insane and they always experiment with new items all the time.  We're so happy we've found this hidden jem.

Oh wow!  Virtuoso is ALWAYS 5 stars for our family, but that's only because we can't rate them at 6... or 10!  10! would be appropriate.

We have NEVER enjoyed such wonderful baked goods!  We ordered several items to complement our Thanksgiving dinner, but I'm reporting today on the pecan 🥧!  Oh my!!! 😋👍

✅ I could spend all day telling you how AMAZING & DELICIOUS the food is here!🥮🍪🥧🍮 I didn’t take any photos of the treats because I eat them before I leave the parking lot, and I’m not kidding Haha. 👌 So many different kinds that are fresh daily and they change often enough so you can always try something new! Don’t hesitate to go, seriously ✅

This place is so delicious. I have never seen so many layers in a croissant. My favorite is the almond, but honestly everything is amazing. The staff are friendly , helpful and energetic. I find this super awesome since they go to work so early every morning. One of my favorite businesses in our little town.
Must try everything! If you live in Charlotte it is definitely worth the drive. Eat there, bring home, repeat!
We love everything we have tried here and we have tried a lot of things. Some of my favorites are their focaccia breads, bagel bombs, chocolate croissants and the danishes.
Very very good!❤ Love that the coffee flavors are all house made!
I love this place! Everything is so delicious and the staff is just the best!
Virtuoso makes the best chocolate dairy-free cookies you'll ever have. And Amelya is the bomb. Love this place!
Staff has always been friendly and food has been excellent!  You will not be disappointed!

You could not ask for a better or more friendly staff, several choices the day we went. Everything we got was amazing. You can tell this is not some mass produced product. This is top quality with that wonderful homemade right out of the oven flavor. Do yourself a favor and stop by soon, you will understand why they have the following they do!
The perfect place for an amazing pastry and coffee.  Plus great outdoor seating with some play areas to entertain the kids.
Amazing little bakery, if you're within 100 miles this should be on your itinerary!

The freaking cutest. I love this place. Just one smell and you want one of everything. Love that the bakery rotates and makes something new each day. I could rave about this bakery all day long but I’m too busy eating their treats right now.
Best. Cinnamon. Rolls. Ever. Everything else is great too, but the cinnamon rolls are literally the best I’ve ever had.
Amazing pastries!

This bakery is absolutely outrageous. I can't even put into words how incredible these pastries/bread are. They are always changing the menu which means I always have a new favorite. Staff is friendly and fun and I highly recommend paying this place a visit! 🤤

This place will blow your mind. It's literally one of a kind and I'm not joking when I say that I've never had baked goods this delicious. Couldn't recommend any higher, you've gotta try it for yourself.
Awesome staff!!!

Absolutely amazing local bakery with different features everyday! The stuffed English muffin is by far a family favorite! Recently had a pineapple peach danish and it was absolutely AMAZING. Staff is always kind and pleasant. Espresso drink needs a little help though.
Highly recommend! We had a couple pastries and coffee. They were all great but any that include their croissant dough is top of the list! Layers on layers on layers. Will definitely go back.
Amazing food!  The sausage wrapped in English muffin is wonderful!  Stop in, you won't regret it!
Best caramel latte Ive had that wasn't in my own coffee shop! The bread and pastries are fabulous. I had a bacon cheddar brioche, a croissant and a loaf of sourdough and each was excellent!
Go here if you want excellent banana bread, fabulous chocolate brownies, and refreshingly delicious iced chai tea and iced coffee!! A gem in Waxhaw! A new favorite for us, and great service!
They have some delicious pastries. Just wish things moved a little quicker inside. We went on a Saturday and there was a line. Overall, great sweets and coffee though.
You walk in and the smell of this place is HEAVENLY!! Customer service was amazing, coffee delicious and pastries  are scrumptious!!
You want to buy the best bread and pastries come here
Very busy always. Pastries are delicious.
This place.... is perfect. Just perfect.

Top quality bakery all round. Their selection is amazing and it’s served with a huge smile from everyone there. Jennie was awesome and took customer service to another level. Super Impressed and Highly recommend this place to anyone!!
Love everything they make. The sourdough is awesome. Picked up an order of hot cross buns today and they are the best! Totally exceeded my expectations.
Great coffee and pastries! The staff was super great and understanding when I mentioned my peanut allergy. I also really appreciate the milk alternatives available too!
AMAZING coffee and pastries!!!
Pastries are amazing but coffee was really nasty, they add plain whole milk . Paying $6 for a small cup of coffee for  a low quality ingredients is a reap off .
Waxhaw is so lucky to have this gem. Well worth the visit...just for the viennoissrie alone - hand laminated (not machine rolled.)
Love the place, very kind people and service
Great place. Staff extremely friendly and helpful. Great sourdough bread. The rye bread was excellent. The pastries were delicious.

We grab breakfast from the bakery every Saturday morning and sometimes during the week! I also will get a bunch of different things for team meetings for my law firm. The bagel bombs, stuffed English muffins, crescent cups, and danishes are our favorite!!! Absolutely never disappointed!
Delightful staff and delicious breads, croissants, treats, coffee and teas!

It is hard to leave this wonderful bakery without a bag full of goodies. The sourdough breads are perfect for sandwiches and morning toast with jelly. My kids are very picky but love the bagel bombs and croissants.  For those with a sweet tooth, you have to try it the twice baked croissants and brown sugar cookies.  I could go on and on but you really need to stop by and try something. I promise you won’t be disappointed.
Always warm and kind and great bread/ pasteries/ goodies and coffee.

I just got home from the most amazing bakery! Virtuoso breadworks, you absolutely captured my full attention. We got a jalapeño bagel bomb to which my husband said was one of the best things he’s ever eaten (mind you it was still warm and melty when we got home). We also got regular and apple cinnamon rolls, an almond croissant, Irish cheddar sourdough loaf and coffee. Every single last crumb was delicious. And the coffee too, probably the best latte I’ve ever had. So smooth. I myself am also a baker and am ALWAYS disappointed when I get bread and pastries outside of my own kitchen because I never feel like they are as good as my own. Today was different. VIRTUOSO you will now forever be in my weekly lineup. We probably will have to get one of everything until we try it all. My husband seriously wants to go back and get every jalapeño bomb in the case. And if what I said wasn’t enough already, the staff was so absolutely friendly and you could tell instantly that they have a LOVE for their craft. Please stop at all costs and support this amazing business. We’ll probably be back this afternoon.

Stopped in today after hearing my co-worker rave about this place. Certainly worth the drive from Fort Mill! Gorgeous loaves of sourdough bread and tasty pastries. The raspberry cruffin was divine! The staff are just as sweet as their creations. Will be visiting again very soon!
Love the Lemon thumbprints

After hearing lots of great things about this place, we decided to check it out. It's a bit of a drive for us, so we planned a hike in the area too.

Covid-19: I was actually not very comfortable here. We waited in line for probably 20-25 minutes in a very small, and pretty crowded converted house. The worst part was that they have couches for people to eat at right next to where you have to wait in line. While we were there, two people were just sitting on them talking, not wearing masks (they had clearly finished eating a while ago). Given the small area and that there's no way to get takeout quickly, it would be safer if they didn't have people eating inside right now.

Once we got to the front of the line, the staff was very friendly and described everything they had. We ended up getting a sourdough english muffin that was stuffed with sausage, bread pudding, and a dulce de leche cruffin.

The english muffin sandwich thing was delicious. It wasn't served warm, but we still loved it cold. I might take it home and warm it up next time. The bread pudding was pretty good too.

The cruffin was not good. It was very dry and didn't have a lot of dulce de leche.

I'd love to come back and try some more of their savory items because I think that's where they really shine.

I'm not rateing this place on the food I'm rateting this place on the times that it's open and closed worse then bankers hours cannot believe on a Sunday morning closed never heard of a bakery being closed on a Sunday morning
reviews_data.owner_answer: We have 3 children at home and believe in making time for family. All of our products are handmade, in house and we are old school. If we were open on Sunday, we would never have a day off. I'm sorry that you feel the need to rate is based on when we are open and not on the quality of our products. We would be more than happy to suggest some of our items and give reheat instructions so you can enjoy our products on a Sunday. Also, there aren't any banks around here open on a Sunday, so 7-530 5 days a week seems pretty reasonable for a small family owned and operated business.

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious treats. Unique coffee and tea selection

So many delicious choices. Hard to just get one thing! Today's picks: English muffins, raspberry cheese Danish, butter croissant, chocolate croissant, savory stuffed croissant. Can't wait to get them in my belly 😊
Great coffee. Great cinnamon raisin bread. Julia was wonderful.

We must have come when they were having an off day. There was only one other patron in the store and the staff took a while to acknowledge that we were there.  However, once we were acknowledged the lady was extremely friendly. The selections were very limited by 2pm on a Tuesday.  We didn’t buy any bread products due to limited selection so we bought drinks. The drinks were small, overpriced and tasted watered down (lacked flavor). Overall for the price I would not go back.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the feedback. There are days we unexpectedly sell out of many things very early. Our apologies that there wasn't a better selection available! We recently installed a brand new espresso machine and are working on our training program and drink menu to ensure this doesn't happen again.

reviews_data.review_text: A co-worker just brought us some cookies as a Christmas gift and o-m-g!! They are SO delicious! Way to go. Highly recommend!

Great food/coffee,  friendly staff - recommend avoiding if busy during the pandemic, as there is basically no way to effectively distance inside. I stop by, and if busy, I just leave and come back another time.
Great pastries!

Love this little gem! Everyone in there is so friendly and so caring. Love that they actually take the time to ask you how your day/week is going (even when they are busy and don’t rush you out). The BEST pastries and breads ever and best chai lattes.

The ladies here were extremely inviting, the coffee was great, and there so many options for pastries and sweets. I will definitely be making this a frequently visited local business. The smells alone make a stop worth while!
The staff is wonderful. Will gladly drive all the way to Waxhaw for this place.
Best pastries in Union County
Most bakeries produce good cookies because most cookies are good. Their cookies are, “out of this world  fabulous! Try them all!
Excellent Staff, excellent food!!
Nice to have an amazing place in my awesome hometown of Waxhaw!  Their chocolate croissants are huge and delicious!

My favorite bakery in waxhaw! My intention is to go in for one pastry and I always I end up leaving with a whole box because everything always looks so good. And it always tastes so good. The best quality & best ingredients make this bakery a star!!
I had the everything bagel bomb, it might be the most amazing bagel I've ever had. The staff is super nice and helpful. My daughter has a nut allergy and they were able to accommodate her needs

Holy Smokes!!! This is the real deal. I live in Charlotte and make it a point to drive out and devour these delightful, delicious, fresh gifts from the bakery gods. Seriously though, the owners are humble, honest and talented as they come. Their love is poured into each croissant, cruffin and sourdough loaf. Don't get me started on the Stuffed English Muffins and the Bagel Bombs!!! Virtuoso gives 2020 hope to the community that we all need to treat ourselves.

Stopped by for coffee and a sweet treat. Had a cheese struesel croissant, took home a loaf of cinnamon raisin bread as well. The croissant was  melt in my mouth, delicious! The raisin bread was light, fluffy, with a nice crust. Compliments to the Baker. The employees were friendly and helpful. They took time to tell me about each of the bakery items. I will return!
